0stopped%20short%20of%20fully%20backing%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%2014%20Democratic%20members%20of%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives%20have%20openly%20urged%20the%20man%20who%20beat%20Trump%20four%20years%20ago%20to%20drop%20out%2C%20along%20with%20one%20Democratic%20senator.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20poll%20released%20on%20Thursday%20showed%20more%20than%20half%20of%20Democrats%20say%20Biden%20should%20end%20his%20bid%20for%20a%20second%20term%2C%20and%20two-thirds%20of%20Americans%20believe%20he%20should%20quit%20the%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20former%20president%20and%20the%20incumbent%20remain%20in%20a%20dead%20heat%20on%2046%20percent%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Washington%20Post-ABC%20News-Ipsos%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden's%20campaign%20was%20however%20quietly%20testing%20the%20strength%20of%20Harris%20in%20a%20potential%20match-up%20against%20Trump%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20president's%20longtime%20aides%20are%20meanwhile%20discussing%20how%20to%20convince%20him%20that%20he%20should%20step%20aside%2C%20the%20paper%20also%20said%2C%20citing%20anonymous%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20said%20the%20report%20was%20%26quot%3Bunequivocally%26quot%3B%20false.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20once-talkative%20Biden%20has%20given%20fewer%20news%20conferences%20than%20his%20predecessors%2C%20but%20he%20was%20speaking%20at%20unusual%20length%20Thursday%20in%20what%20his%20aides%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bbig%20boy%26quot%3B%20press%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20has%20called%20his%20debate%20meltdown%20a%20%26quot%3Bbad%20night%2C%26quot%3B%20blaming%20it%20on%20a%20cold%20and%20jet%20lag.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Clooney%20tried%20to%20torpedo%20the%20narrative%20that%20it%20was%20a%20one-off%2C%20saying%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bdevastating%26quot%3B%20to%20admit%20but%20the%20signs%20were%20also%20clear%20at%20a%20June%2015%20fundraiser%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20he%20host