2%3EGaza%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20live%20with%20my%20husband%20and%20three%20kids%20in%20a%20mixed%20city%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fisrael%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIsrael%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20Jews%2C%20Muslims%2C%20and%20Christians%20live%20together.%20I%20moved%20here%20over%20a%20decade%20ago%20from%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJerusalem%2C%20while%20officially%20considered%20a%20mixed%20city%2C%20largely%20consists%20of%20religiously%20homogeneous%20neighborhoods%2C%20making%20apartment%20blocks%20with%20Jews%2C%20Muslims%2C%20and%20Christians%20living%20together%20%E2%80%94%20like%20mine%20%E2%80%94%20far%20less%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20the%20diversity%20in%20my%20city.%20I%20love%20that%20my%20children%20attend%20Christmas%20parades%20and%20are%20aware%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20as%20I%20write%20this%20essay%20on%20a%20June%20afternoon%2C%20our%20neighbors%20are%20celebrating%20the%20Muslim%20holiday%20of%20Eid%20al%20Adha.%20But%20like%20everything%20else%20in%20this%20neck%20of%20the%20woods%2C%20living%20side%20by%20side%20can%20sometimes%20be%20fraught%20with%20complexities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20news%20started%20emerging%20of%20what%20took%20place%20on%20October%207%2C%20I%20did%20everything%20in%20my%20power%20to%20protect%20my%20three%20children%2C%20especially%20my%20eldest%2C%20a%20highly%20sensitive%208-year-old%20with%20a%20string%20of%20acronyms%20after%20her%20name%20that%20point%20to%20her%20various%20diagnoses.%20I%20made%20sure%20that%20in%20any%20room%20she%20entered%2C%20the%20news%20was%20switched%20off%20%E2%80%94%20no%20small%20feat%20in%20a%20country%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jpost.com%2Fbusiness-and-innovation%2Fall-news%2Farticle-772884%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enews%20consumption%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20basically%20a%20national%20pastime.%20I%20would%20stifle%20any%20conversation%20about%20the%20situation%20by%20family%20members%20that%20was%20within%20her%20earshot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2230574d6a-9cad-487e-bdf7-3ec3338de800%5C%22%3EI%20was%20terrified%20of%20scarring%20her%20for%20life%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20only%20let%20her%20know%20that%20hostages%20had%20been%20taken%20into%20Gaza%20after%20half%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%20including%20almost%20all%20of%20the%20children%20among%20them%20%E2%80%94%20were%20released%2C%20more%20than%2050%20days%20into%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20then%20came%20the%20day%20when%20she%20was%20home%20alone%20in%20our%20apartment%20during%20a%20rocket%20siren.%20It%20was%20inevitable%2C%20really.%20Rockets%20were%20raining%20down%20on%20our%20city%20on%20a%20daily%20basis%2C%20and%20my%20work%20as%20a%20journalist%20meant%20that%20I%20was%20often%20out%20of%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20also%20found%20himself%20working%20around%20the%20clock%20when%20his%20boutique%20hotel%2C%20like%20many%20others%20across%20the%20country%2C%20was%20converted%20overnight%20into%20semi-permanent%20housing%20for%20some%20of%20the%20300%2C000%20internal%20refugees%20fleeing%20Israel's%20northern%20and%20southern%20borders%2C%20which%20were%20under%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20that%20day%2C%20I%20called%20my%20daughter%20as%20soon%20as%20the%20Code%20Red%20app%20on%20my%20phone%20bleeped%2C%20alerting%20me%20to%20an%20incoming%20projectile.%20She%20told%20me%20that%20she%20was%20trying%20to%20close%20the%20iron%20blast%20door%20of%20the%20safe%20room%20but%20that%20it%20was%20too%20heavy%20for%20her.%20She%20said%20it%20matter-of-factly.%20I%20tried%20to%20mask%20the%20rising%20panic%20in%20my%20voice%20as%20I%20told%20her%20to%20try%20again%2C%20harder%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20useless%2C%20so%20I%20told%20her%20to%20go%20into%20the%20stairwell%20of%20our%20building%2C%20where%20there%20were%20no%20windows%20and%20less%20risk%20of%20falling%20shrapnel.%20Buildings%20erected%20in%20Israel%20since%20the%201990s%20have%20%3Ca%2