For%20astronauts%2C%20spending%20that%20much%20time%20in%20spaceflight%20comes%20with%20big%20health%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey'd%20be%20exposed%20to%20high%20levels%20of%20solar%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-energy-radiation-hotspot-space-puzzles-astronomers-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecosmic%20radiation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20harmful%20effects%20of%20zero-gravity%2C%20and%20a%20long%20period%20of%20isolation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpace%20radiation%20is%20arguably%20the%20biggest%20threat.%20Astronauts%20who%20spend%20just%20six%20months%20in%20space%20are%20exposed%20to%20roughly%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20radiation%20as%201%2C000%20chest%20X-rays%2C%20and%20this%20puts%20them%20at%20risk%20for%20cancer%2C%20nervous%20system%20damage%2C%20bone%20loss%2C%20and%20heart%20disease%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-transfer-spinoffs%2Fnasa-funded-space-radiation-research-fights-cancer-on-earth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20NASA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20way%20to%20reduce%20radiation%20exposure%20and%20other%20harmful%20health%20effects%20is%20to%20shorten%20the%20length%20of%20the%20trip%2C%20Troy%20Howe%2C%20president%20of%20Howe%20Industries%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20That's%20why%20he's%20teamed%20up%20with%20NASA%20to%20develop%20the%20Pulsed%20Plasma%20Rocket%20(PPR)%3A%20a%20new%20rocket%20system%20that%20could%20shorten%20a%20round-trip%20to%20Mars%20to%20just%20two%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20technology%20%26quot%3Bholds%20the%20potential%20to%20revolutionize%20space%20exploration%2C%26quot%3B%20NASA%20wrote%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fdirectorates%2Fstmd%2Fniac%2Fniac-studies%2Fpulsed-plasma-rocket-ppr-shielded-fast-transits-for-humans-to-mars%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20could%20one%20day%20take%20humans%20even%20further%20than%20Mars.%3C%2F