n%2C%20the%20level%20required%20for%20a%20population%20to%20maintain%20a%20constant%20size%20in%20the%20long%20run%20without%20migration.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEarly%20childbearing%20has%20harmful%20effects%20on%20young%20mothers%20and%20their%20children.%20In%202024%2C%204.7%20million%20babies%2C%20or%20about%203.5%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20total%20worldwide%2C%20were%20born%20to%20mothers%20under%20age%2018%20-%20%C2%A0and%20some%203.4%20lakh%20to%20girls%20under%20age%2015%20-%20with%20serious%20consequences%20for%20the%20health%20and%20well-being%20of%20both%20the%20young%20mothers%20and%20their%20children.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFollowing%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20global%20life%20expectancy%20is%20rising%20once%20again.%20Globally%2C%20life%20expectancy%20at%20birth%20reached%2073.3%20years%20in%202024%2C%20an%20increase%20of%208.4%20years%20since%201995.%20Further%20reductions%20in%20mortality%20are%20projected%20to%20result%20in%20an%20average%20longevity%20of%20around%2077.4%20years%20globally%20in%202054.%20Since%202022%2C%20life%20expectancy%20has%20returned%20to%20pre-COVID-19%20levels%20in%20nearly%20all%20countries%20and%20areas.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20main%20driver%20of%20global%20population%20increase%20through%20the%20mid-century%20will%20be%20the%20momentum%20created%20by%20growth%20in%20the%20past.%20The%20number%20of%20women%20at%20ages%2015-49%20is%20projected%20to%20grow%20from%20nearly%202%20billion%20in%202024%20to%20a%20peak%20of%20around%202.2%20billion%20in%20the%20late%202050s%2C%20driving%20continued%20growth%20even%20if%20the%20number%20of%20births%20per%20woman%20falls%20to%20the%20replacement%20level.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECountries%20with%20youthful%20populations%20and%20declining%20fertility%20have%20a%20limited%20time%20to%20benefit%20economically%20from%20an%20increasing%20concentration%20of%20population%20in%20the%20working%20ages.%20In%20about%20100%20countries%20or%20areas%2C%20the%20working-age%20population%20(between%2020%20and%2064%20years)%20will%20grow%20through%202054%2C%20offering%20a%20window%20of%20opportunity%20known%20as%20the%20demographic%20dividend.%20To%20capitalise%20on%20this%20opportunity%2C%20countries%20must%20invest%20in%20education%2C%20health%2C%20and%20infrastructure%2C%20and%20implement%20reforms%20to%20create%20jobs%20and%20improve%20government%20efficiency.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBy%202080%2C%20persons%20aged%2065%20or%20older%20will%20outnumber%20children%20under%2018.%20By%20the%20late%202070s%2C%20the%20global%20population%20aged%2065%20and%20older%20is%20projected%20to%20reach%202.2%20billion%2C%20exceeding%20the%20number%20of%20children%20under%2018.%20By%20the%20mid-2030s%2C%20those%20aged%2080%20and%20over%20will%20outnumber%20infants%20(1%20year%20of%20age%20or%20less)%2C%20reaching%20265%20million.%20Countries%20that%20are%20at%20more%20advanced%20stages%20in%20the%20process%20of%20demographic%20ageing%20should%20consider%20the%20use%20of%20technology%20to%20improve%20productivity%20at%20all%20ages.%20They%20should%20also%20design%20more%20opportunities%20for%20lifelong%20learning%20and%20re-training%2C%20support%20multigenerational%20workforces%20and%20create%20opportunities%20to%20extend%20working%20lives%20for%20those%20who%20can%20and%20want%20to%20continue%20working.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFor%20some%20populations%2C%20immigration%20will%20be%20the%20main%20driver%20of%20future%20growth.%20In%2050%20countries%20and%20areas%2C%20immigration%20is%20projected%20to%20attenuate%20the%20decline%20in%20population%20size%20due%20to%20sustained%20low%20levels%20of%20fertility%20and%20an%20older%20age%20structure.%20However%2C%20in%2014%20countries%20and%20areas%20already%20experiencing%20ultra-low%20fertility%2C%20emigration%20is%20likely%20to%20contribute%20to%20reducing%20population%20size%20through%202054.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EGender%20equality%20and%20women's%20empowerment%20help%20to%20counter%20rapid%20population%20growth%20or%20decline.%20Discrimination%20and%20legal%20barriers%20limit%20women%20and%20adolescents'%20access%20to%20sexual%20and%20reproductive%20health%20services.%20Raising%20the%20legal%20marriage%20age%20and%20integrating%20family%20planning%20into%20primary%20health%20care%20can%20enhance%20women's%20education%2C%20economic%20participation%2C%20and%20reduce%20childbearing.%20In%20countries%20where%20populations%20have%20peaked%20already%20or%20are%20likely%20to%20peak%20in%20the%20next%20three%20decades%2C%20policies%20providing%20paid%20parental%20leave%20and%20flexible%20working%20arrangements%2C%20supporting%20affordable%2C%20high-quality%20childcare%2C%20providing%20comprehensive%20care%20for%20an%20ageing%20population%3B%20and%20encouraging%20an%20equal%20distribution%20of%20caregiving%20and%20household%20responsibilities%20between%20men%20and%20women%20can%20improve%20women's%20participation.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720717260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2F610ld0o_population-generic-pixabay_625x300_28_February_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2F65-year-olds-will-outnumber-those-under-18-by-2080-un-population-report-6083075%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20UN%20World%20Population%20Prospects%20report%20said%20the%20world's%20population%20will%20peak%20in%20the%20mid-2080s%2C%20growing%20over%20the%20next%2060%20years%20from%208.2%20billion%20people%20now%20to%2010.3%20billion%20in%20the%20mid-2080s%2C%20and%20will%20return%20to%2010.2%20billion%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20century.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2F65-year-olds-will-outnumber-those-under-18-by-2080-un-population-report-6083075%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2F65-year-olds-will-outnumber-those-under-18-by-2080-un-population-report-6083075%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22a