o%20have%20an%20uninterrupted%20power%20supply.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1720701178.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1720701178-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1720701178-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1720701178-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1720701178-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-356495%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EFor%20Shilpa%20and%20Suneet%2C%20the%20first%20biggest%20transformation%20with%20this%20setup%20was%20to%20have%20an%20uninterrupted%20power%20supply.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20whole%20grid-backed%20setfup%20was%20different%20from%20a%20net-metered%20system.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20the%20difference%20between%20the%20two%2C%20Suneet%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20net-metered%20system%2C%20you%20do%20not%20require%20to%20store%20the%20energy%20and%20feed%20excess%20energy%20to%20the%20grid%20and%20get%20it%20back%20from%20it%20when%20you%20are%20not%20generating%20enough%20power.%20It%20is%20a%20more%20economical%20way%20for%20harnessing%20solar%20energy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20grid-backed%20setup%2C%20we%20do%20not%20feed%20excess%20power%20to%20the%20grid%2C%20we%20instead%20store%20the%20excess%20energy%20and%20use%20it%20during%20non-generation%20hours%2C%20say%20during%20the%20nights%20and%20cloudy%20days.%20We%20have%20our%20own%20backup.%20As%20long%20as%20I%20am%20dependent%20on%20the%20grid%2C%20we%20are%20responsible%20for%20coal-backed%20power%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20the%20major%20production%20of%20electricity%20is%20achieved%20through%20coal%20thermal%20power%20plants%20which%20is%20around%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.coal.nic.in%2Fen%2Fmajor-statistics%2Fgeneration-of-thermal-power-from-raw-coal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E75%20percent%20%3C%2Fa%3Eof%20the%20total%20power%20generation.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20want%20to%20reduce%20your%20carbon%20footprint%2C%20you%20need%20to%20reduce%20your%20dependence%20on%20coal%20and%20thermal%20energy%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBesides%2C%20if%20the%20grid%20in%20the%20net-metre%20system%20decides%20to%20shut%20down%2C%20my%20house%20will%20still%20be%20in%20darkness%20even%20though%20I%20am%20generating%20power%20from%20solar%20energy.%20The%20grid-backed%20system%20helps%20us%20create%20power%20backup%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESelf-dependent%20on%20energy%20%26amp%3B%20water%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20to%20be%20noted%20that%20the%20couple%20has%20not%20given%20up%20on%20their%20electricity%20metre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1_11zon-1720701302.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20couple%20planned%20a%20grid%20backed%20solar%20photovoltaic%20(PV)%20system%20in%20the%20house%20with%20a%2015%20kWp%20capacity.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1_11zon-1720701302.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1_11zon-1720701302-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1_11zon-1720701302-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Fsolar-1_11zon-1720701302-768x402.jpg%2076